      <h1 class='title'>Employment Tribunal Service (Performance Targets)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 20 July 2004 vol 424 cc15-6WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_15ws' title='Col. 15WS &mdash; HC Deb 20 July 2004 vol 424 c15WS' name='column_15ws' href='#column_15ws' rel='bookmark'>15WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040720_CWS_10'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-gerry-sutcliffe' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040720_CWS_10' title='Link to this speech by Mr Gerry Sutcliffe' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-gerry-sutcliffe" title="Mr Gerry Sutcliffe">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Trade and Industry (Mr. Gerry Sutcliffe)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The employment tribunals service has published its annual report and accounts for 2003&#x2014;04 today. Copies have been laid before Parliament and will be placed on the ETS website at<span class="underline">http://www.ets.gov.uk.</span></p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_16ws' title='Col. 16WS &mdash; HC Deb 20 July 2004 vol 424 c16WS' name='column_16ws' href='#column_16ws' rel='bookmark'>16WS</a><p>I have set the employment tribunals service the following targets for 2004&#x2013;05:</p><p><span class="italic">Quality</span>
          <q>75 per cent. of single employment tribunal cases to a first hearing within 26 weeks of receipt.</q>
          <q>Minimum to be achieved by all offices in relation to above target: 65 per cent.</q>
          <q>85 per cent. of employment tribunal decisions issued within four weeks of the final hearing.</q>
          <q>85 per cent. of employment tribunal users satisfied with the service offered by ETS.</q>
          <q>75 per cent of appeals to EAT to a first hearing within 26 weeks of receipt.</q></p><p><span class="italic">Efficiency</span>
          <q>Three per cent. real terms reduction in employment tribunal administrative unit costs.</q></p><p>In addition to these key targets:</p><p><span class="italic">Finance</span>
          <q>Pay 100 per cent. of invoices within 30 days of receipt of goods or services or a valid invoice, whichever is the later.</q></p><p><span class="italic">Questions delegated to the Chief Executive</span>
          <q>Reply within 10 working days to all letters from Members of Parliament delegated for the Chief Executive's reply.</q></p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
